This article reflects on the last conversation with John Lewis before his death, where he emphasized the importance of continuing the work of healing and uniting the nation. The authors, Jill and the article's writer, have been reflecting on this conversation in their six months in office. They acknowledge the progress made in battling the pandemic and rebuilding the economy but recognize that there is still work to be done to ensure equity, healthcare as a right, a dignified economy, and equal justice under the law. They also highlight the need to protect voting rights, as there have been recent attacks on voting rights and the integrity of elections. They call on Congress to pass the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. They urge the nation to come together and act, forming a coalition of Americans from various backgrounds and political parties. They emphasize the importance of continuing to fight for freedom and democracy, guided by John Lewis' spirit.